28
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:23,070
This is the power of the microservices, and it is allows to deploy new functionality without any downtime.

29
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:26,460
That means independent microservices.

30
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:31,080
Each service can be deployed and updated independently, providing more flexibility.

31
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:39,580
An error in a microservices only has effect on one specific service that doesn't affect the entire application.

32
00:02:39,610 --> 00:02:45,520
Also, adding new features to microservice application is easier than a monolithic application, whether

33
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,100
the application is very large or very small.

34
00:02:48,130 --> 00:02:53,830
Adding new features and maintaining existing code is easy, because it is sufficient to make changes

35
00:02:53,830 --> 00:02:56,080
only within relevant microservices.

36
00:02:56,870 --> 00:03:02,120
Another good reason is required to independently scale a portion of application.

37
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:08,510
If your application required to independently scale a portion of the application, then microservices

38
00:03:08,510 --> 00:03:12,350
are an excellent choice for this kind of operations and applications.

